      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="brain" size={22} /></div><strong>Serotonin Enhancement</strong><p>HCA increases serotonin availability, which promotes satiety (feeling full), reduces emotional/stress eating, and may improve mood during caloric restriction. This appetite management effect may be more practically valuable than fat-synthesis inhibition.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="target" size={22} /></div><strong>Glycogen Redirection</strong><p>By blocking fat synthesis from carbohydrates, HCA may redirect carbohydrate metabolism toward glycogen storage in muscles and liver, potentially improving exercise capacity and endurance alongside weight management efforts.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="clock" size={22} /></div><strong>Pre-Meal Timing</strong><p>HCA must be present in the bloodstream before carbohydrate-rich meals for effective enzyme inhibition. Take 30-60 minutes before meals on an empty stomach. The divided pre-meal dosing schedule is critical for optimal results.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <p>Important context: while garcinia cambogia shows statistically significant effects on body weight, <strong>the magnitude of weight loss is modest (approximately 2 pounds more than placebo)</strong>. No supplement replaces the fundamental requirement of caloric deficit for meaningful weight loss. Garcinia cambogia is best viewed as a modest adjunct to dietary changes and regular physical activity — not as a primary weight loss intervention. Set realistic expectations and prioritize sustainable lifestyle changes.</p>
      <cite>Onakpoya et al. — Journal of Obesity (2011 Meta-Analysis)</cite>
    </div>

