    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Garcinia Cambogia Gummies</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Does garcinia cambogia actually work for weight loss?</summary><p>Meta-analysis of 12 RCTs shows approximately 2 pounds more weight loss than placebo over 2-12 weeks. Real but modest effect. Works through ATP-citrate lyase inhibition and serotonin-mediated appetite suppression. Best as adjunct to diet + exercise, not standalone.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What is HCA and how does it work?</summary><p>Hydroxycitric acid inhibits ATP-citrate lyase (blocking carb-to-fat conversion), increases serotonin (reducing appetite/emotional eating), and may redirect metabolism toward glycogen storage. Need 50-60% HCA standardization for meaningful enzyme inhibition.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How much garcinia cambogia should I take?</summary><p>1,500-3,000mg extract (50-60% HCA) daily, divided into 2-3 pre-meal doses. Take 30-60 minutes before meals on empty stomach. Most gummies provide 500-1,000mg per serving. Higher HCA percentage means more active compound per milligram.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Is garcinia cambogia safe?</summary><p>Generally safe at recommended doses for up to 12 weeks. Rare liver toxicity reports mostly involved adulterated products with hidden ingredients. Choose pure garcinia without proprietary blends. Third-party testing is essential. Do not exceed 2,800mg/day. Monitor liver function if using long-term.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>When should I take garcinia cambogia gummies?</summary><p>30-60 minutes before meals on empty stomach. Divide daily dose across 2-3 meals (before breakfast, lunch, dinner). HCA must be circulating before carbs are consumed. Taking with food reduces absorption. Do not take before bed.</p></details>

